Variables
- local, instance & static

int data = 50;

LOCAL VARIABLE
- variable declared inside the body of the method.
- Can use only within that method.

INSTANCE VARIABLE
- variable declared inside the class but outside the body of the method.
- not shared among instances

STATIC VARIABLE
- Cannot be local.
- Can share it among all the instances of the class

1. Primitive data types: The primitive data types include boolean, char, byte, short, int, long, float and double.
2. Non-primitive data types: The non-primitive data types include Classes, Interfaces, and Arrays.
